To find the union of set A and set B, we combine all the unique elements from both sets. 

Set A = {1, 2, 3}
Set B = {2, 4, 6}

Union of set A and set B: {1, 2, 3, 4, 6}

Now, to find a superset of the union of set A and set B, we need a set that contains all the elements of the union and possibly more elements. One example of a superset would be:

Superset: {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8}

Note that there can be multiple different supersets, as long as they contain all the elements of the union of set A and set B.
